7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1130, L.D. 1695, “An Act to Provide
10 Law Enforcement Agencies with an Anti-sex-trafficking and Commercial Sexual
11 Exploitation Protocol”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Require Law Enforcement Agencies to Adopt Written Policies Regarding
14 Sex Trafficking and Commercial Sexual Exploitation'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §2803-B, sub-§1, ¶N, as amended by PL 2023, c. 394, Pt. A,
18 §8, is further amended to read:
19 N. Unannounced execution of search warrants; and
20 Sec. 2. 25 MRSA §2803-B, sub-§1, ¶O, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 394, Pt. A, §9,
21 is amended to read:
22 O. By January 1, 2024, the confidentiality of attorney-client communications, which
23 must include, at a minimum, processes to protect and ensure confidentiality of
24 attorney‑client communications and processes to be followed in the event that there is
25 a breach of attorney‑client confidentiality.; and
26 Sec. 3. 25 MRSA §2803-B, sub-§1, ¶P is enacted to read:
27 P. Persons who are believed to be experiencing sex trafficking or commercial sexual
28 exploitation.'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
